<paragraph id="8B8536C2E51E926C434EA0FFDAE5302A" blockId="5.[125,230,496,520]" box="[125,230,496,520]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E51E926C434EA0FFDAE5302A" box="[125,230,496,520]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8536C2E51E926C434EA32EDE973099" blockId="5.[125,1172,545,699]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E51E926C434EA32EDB99301B" authority="Sluys" authorityName="Sluys" authorityYear="2005" box="[125,410,545,569]" family="Uteriporidae" genus="Miroplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="paulula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E51E926C434EA32EDB4D301B" box="[125,334,545,569]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Miroplana paulula</emphasis>
Sluys
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27D57ABE51E926C4299A32ED80A301B" box="[426,521,545,569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by three pigmented transverse bands, with the anterior band located in front of the eyes, a genito-intestinal duct between copulatory bursa and the gut, and one pair of large testes located between the brain and the root of the pharynx. The species differs from its congener by the absence of spines in the ejaculatory duct and lack of a communication between bursal canal and male atrium.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF45664AE51E926C434EA769DBE534B1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221459" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5221459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221459/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" startId="5.[125,194,1638,1657]" targetBox="[295,997,773,1601]" targetPageId="5">
